Introduction

Chocolat, commonly stylized as ChoColat, was a South Korean girl group created by Paramount Music in 2011.

The group's name stems from the idea that each member is reminiscent of a different type of chocolate. The name of the group was initially going to be "Chocolate", but there was already a group with that name, so Paramount Music decided to use the French word chocolat instead.

The group consists of mixed-race members. The group became inactive in 2013. Melanie confirmed in an interview that the group members' contracts had concluded in February 2017 and the group had disbanded.
